description: The table SYNTHETIC.WEBINARS represents a collection of webinar records, each uniquely identified by the WEBINAR_ID primary key. Each entry in the table provides details about a specific webinar, including its name and description, along with several attribute fields (such as CAMPAIGN_136_ATTR_0 and WEBINAR_136_ATTR_1) possibly used for categorization or additional configuration. As there are no foreign keys or references from other tables, this table appears to function independently within the database, primarily serving as a repository of webinar information.

columns.name: WEBINAR_ID
columns.description: This column uniquely identifies each webinar in the database. The sequential numeric values suggest that it tracks the order in which webinars are recorded.

columns.name: NAME
columns.description: This column represents the naming or labeling of different webinars, indicated by their sequential numbering. It appears to reflect a series or catalog of webinar events.

columns.name: DESCRIPTION
columns.description: This column contains textual summaries or titles for specific webinars, likely indicating their content or topic. Purpose unclear from available data.

columns.name: CAMPAIGN_136_ATTR_0
columns.description: This column indicates whether a specific attribute related to campaign 136 was present during webinars. It consistently captures a yes or no condition for each instance.

columns.name: WEBINAR_136_ATTR_3
columns.description: This column likely indicates a binary status or preference associated with webinars, such as availability or a specific feature being enabled or disabled. Purpose unclear from available data.
